Tax expert and columnist Barbara Curson's experience includes a stint at the South Africa Revenue Service. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tax filing season starts on Monday and SARS Commissioner Edward Kieswetter has encouraged taxpayers to submit their income tax returns via eFiling. This year, taxpayers who meet the following criteria need not submit a tax return: READ: SARS increases tax return threshold Branch filing closes on 31 October 2019, eFiling closes on 4 December 2019 and provisional taxpayers have until 31 January 2020 to file via eFiling.